# Synergetics.ai AI Agent & Digital Goods Marketplace

Build a production-grade, two-sided marketplace platform with Buyer Marketplace, Seller Portal, Admin Dashboard, and API Server as a Turborepo monorepo.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **This is an extremely large project.** I'll build it incrementally across multiple phases. Each phase will produce working, runnable code before moving to the next. Phase 1-4 are the foundation; Phases 5-10 layer on top. I'll verify at each phase boundary.

> [!WARNING]
> **External service dependencies** — Clerk, Stripe, Elasticsearch, NATS, ClickHouse, MongoDB require API keys or running instances. I'll stub/mock these integrations so the app runs locally without them, with clear `.env.example` documentation for production setup.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Scope management** — Full production deployment of all features would take a team months. I'll implement all specified features with proper architecture, types, and UI, but some external integrations (Persona KYC, Visa, CoinGecko live feeds) will be well-structured stubs ready for real API keys.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: Monorepo Foundation

#### [NEW] Root Configuration Files
- `package.json` — pnpm workspace root with shared scripts
- `turbo.json` — Turborepo pipeline config (build, dev, lint, test, type-check)
- `pnpm-workspace.yaml` — workspace definition
- `tsconfig.base.json` — shared TypeScript strict config
- `.eslintrc.js` — shared ESLint with TypeScript rules
- `.prettierrc` — Prettier config
- `.env.example` — all environment variables documented
- `.gitignore`

#### [NEW] `packages/types/`
Shared Zod schemas + TypeScript types for all entities: User, Seller, Listing, Order, Cart, Subscription, Review, Invoice, Transaction, Wallet, ApiKey, Message, Category, etc. All API request/response schemas.

#### [NEW] `packages/utils/`
Shared utilities: currency formatting, date helpers, slugify, crypto address validation, pagination helpers, error classes.

#### [NEW] `packages/ui/`
shadcn/ui component library with dark theme. Components: Button, Card, Input, Select, Dialog, Table, Badge, Avatar, Tabs, Dropdown, Toast, Sidebar, DataTable, Chart wrappers, and custom marketplace components (PriceDisplay, RatingStars, CategoryCard, ListingCard, WalletConnect).

#### [NEW] `packages/db/`
Drizzle ORM schema for 25+ PostgreSQL tables with full relations, indexes, constraints. Migration files. Seed data script with realistic demo data. MongoDB/Mongoose schemas for audit_logs, listing_metadata, analytics_events.

#### [NEW] `packages/wallet/`
Web3 wallet utilities: EVM (wagmi/viem) and Solana (@solana/wallet-adapter) connection, SIWE message generation/verification, transaction builders, balance queries.

#### [NEW] `packages/x402/`
x402 protocol client: payment header generation, facilitator client (verify/settle calls), resource access with auto-payment.

#### [NEW] `packages/api-client/`
Typed API client generated from OpenAPI spec. Axios-based with interceptors for auth, error handling, retry logic.

---

### Phase 2: Database Schema

#### [NEW] `packages/db/src/schema/`
Complete Drizzle ORM schemas covering all 25+ entities:
- `users.ts` — users, wallets, notification_preferences, api_keys
- `sellers.ts` — sellers, seller_team_members
- `listings.ts` — listings, listing_media, pricing, categories, collections, collection_items
- `orders.ts` — orders, order_items, subscriptions
- `commerce.ts` — cart, cart_items, invoices, reviews
- `finance.ts` — transactions (unified ledger), payouts, disputes, platform_credits
- `messaging.ts` — messages, message_threads
- `audit.ts` — audit_logs

All with: indexes, unique constraints, check constraints, created_at/updated_at defaults, soft delete (deleted_at), and full Drizzle relations.

#### [NEW] `packages/db/src/seed.ts`
Seed script creating: 50 users, 10 sellers, 200 listings across 6 categories, sample orders, reviews, and transactions.

#### [NEW] `packages/db/src/mongo/`
Mongoose schemas for flexible document storage.

---

### Phase 3: API Server (Fastify)

#### [NEW] `apps/api/`
Full Fastify 5.x API server with:
- **Middleware:** Auth (Clerk JWT verification), CORS, rate limiting, request logging (pino), correlation IDs, error handler
- **Routes:** All endpoint groups (/auth, /listings, /categories, /cart, /checkout, /me, /seller, /admin, /x402, /webhooks)
- **Services:** Business logic layer for each domain
- **OpenAPI:** Auto-generated spec via @fastify/swagger + zod-to-openapi
- **Jobs:** BullMQ background job processors (email, indexing, payouts)
- **Health:** /health endpoint for all services

---

### Phase 4: Marketplace Frontend (Buyer-Facing)

#### [NEW] `apps/marketplace/`
Next.js 15 App Router with:
- **Layout:** Dark theme, glassmorphism nav, responsive sidebar, footer
- **Homepage:** Animated hero, featured listings grid, trending, new arrivals, top sellers, category cards
- **Category Pages:** Faceted filters (price, rating, model, blockchain, sort), listing grid
- **Search:** Full-text search with autocomplete dropdown
- **Product Detail Page:** Media gallery, pricing with currency toggle, subscribe/buy CTA, version history, seller card, reviews, related listings
- **3D Preview:** React Three Fiber viewer for avatars/wearables
- **Cart:** Mixed items support, quantity management
- **Checkout:** Multi-step with payment method selection
- **Buyer Hub:** Dashboard, purchases, subscriptions, wallet, invoices, messages, API keys, security
- **Auth Pages:** Sign in/up with Clerk + Web3 wallet connect

---

### Phase 5: Seller Portal

#### [NEW] `apps/seller-portal/`
Next.js 15 App Router with:
- **Onboarding Wizard:** 4-step flow (business info → KYB → Stripe Connect → first listing)
- **Dashboard:** Revenue cards, recent orders, subscriber count, alert banners
- **Listings:** Full CRUD with Tiptap rich text, drag-drop media, variant/tier management, pricing engine, draft/published/archived states, version changelog
- **Bulk Ops:** CSV/JSON import/export
- **Orders:** Table with fulfillment status, refund initiation
- **Subscriptions:** Subscriber list, churn indicators
- **Finance:** Revenue charts (Recharts), transaction ledger, payout settings, tax docs
- **Team:** Invite members, RBAC roles, activity log
- **Analytics:** Sales charts, conversion funnel, MRR, churn, LTV, cohort analysis
- **Compliance:** KYB status, DMCA management, audit log
- **Messaging:** Buyer communication, support tickets

---

### Phase 6: Admin Dashboard

#### [NEW] `apps/admin/`
Next.js 15 App Router with:
- User management, listing moderation queue, financial overview, dispute management, platform analytics, system health, configuration panels

---

### Phase 7: Payment Integrations

Implement across `apps/api/` and frontend apps:
- Stripe Connect (multi-party), Billing, Checkout, Tax, Webhooks
- Web3 wallet payments (EVM + Solana)
- x402 protocol facilitator + client
- Visa API stub
- Synergetics Pay (internal balance)
- Unified transaction ledger

---

### Phase 8: Testing

- Unit tests (Vitest) in `packages/*/` and `apps/api/`
- Integration tests (Vitest + Supertest) for API endpoints
- E2E tests (Playwright) for registration, listing creation, checkout

---

### Phase 9: Infrastructure

#### [NEW] `infrastructure/`
- Multi-stage Dockerfiles (dev + prod) for each app
- `docker-compose.yml` — full local stack
- Helm charts for Kubernetes
- Terraform modules for AWS (EKS, RDS, ElastiCache, S3, CloudFront, Route53, ACM, IAM)
- GitHub Actions CI/CD (PR checks, staging, production)
- Nginx reverse proxy config

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
1. **TypeScript compilation:** `pnpm turbo type-check` — all packages and apps compile with strict mode
2. **Lint:** `pnpm turbo lint` — all code passes ESLint rules
3. **Unit tests:** `pnpm turbo test` — Vitest tests pass for business logic in packages and API
4. **Build:** `pnpm turbo build` — all apps and packages build successfully

### Browser Verification (after each phase)
1. **Phase 4:** Navigate to marketplace at `http://localhost:3000`, verify homepage renders with hero, listings, categories. Test search, product detail page, cart, and checkout flow.
2. **Phase 5:** Navigate to seller portal at `http://localhost:3001`, verify onboarding wizard, dashboard, listing CRUD, analytics charts.
3. **Phase 6:** Navigate to admin at `http://localhost:3002`, verify user management, moderation queue, analytics.

### Manual Verification
- Run `docker-compose up` and verify all services start
- Seed the database and verify data appears in marketplace
- Test responsive layout at mobile/tablet/desktop breakpoints
